# Cross-pollination rule (multi-pair-trading-agent)

Apply this rule when the trading agent produces an observation that would change a decision in the dissertation or portfolio app.

## What to do

1. Open `/Users/the1finix/Documents/GitHub/brain-box/meta/shared-findings.md`.
2. Append a row:

   ```
   | YYYY-MM-DD | life/finance-research/multi-pair-trading-agent | <affected node(s)> | <finding> | <action> |
   ```

3. Append a `## Session log` bullet to:
   - `/Users/the1finix/Documents/GitHub/brain-box/school/surrey-msc-ai/dissertation-eeem004.md` (if dissertation affected)
   - `/Users/the1finix/Documents/GitHub/brain-box/life/finance-research/global-portfolio-assistant.md` (if portfolio app affected)

## Examples of cross-affecting findings

- Broker fills show >100ms slippage on session opens → dissertation backtest fill model needs Beta-distributed slippage.
- Asian session false breakouts on EURUSD → flag pattern for finance-research-experiments validation, possibly demote in dissertation feature set.
- Demo MT5 connection drops 0.3% of orders → real-world reliability claim in dissertation must be tempered.
- New zone-detection heuristic outperforms baseline → propose adoption in DRL state encoder.

## Hard rule

Do not log to the ledger findings that don't cross pillars. Keep eurusd-only tweaks inside this repo.
